headline.main: Jesse Owens Dies of Cancer at 66; Hero of the 1936 Berlin Olympics; Jesse Owens Dies of Lung Cancer at 66 No Response to Drugs Father Was a Sharecropper 10 Blacks on Team Celebrated as a Speaker

abstract: Jesse Owens, hero of '36 Berlin Olympics, dies at age 66; career sketch; portrait; illus (L)
snippet: Jesse Owens, whose four gold medals at the 1936 Olympic Games in Berlin made him perhaps the greatest and most famous athlete in track and field history, died of lung cancer yesterday in Tucson, Ariz. He was 66 years old.
